The company will finance it using 60 percent of the SGD 66 million it raised this week on the Singapore Exchange.
While some discount lenders have come under fire for their high interest rates, Ms. Yeah says that the mortgage not only offers lower rates than other lenders, but also does not directly increase debt.
"Customers are stopping items they already own, and monetizing personal assets does not increase household debt", he says.
In society, asset pledges are increasingly accepted as a means of securing short-term, secure financing.
