He also admitted that the YMCA's opening statement was inaccurate in stating that external audits were carried out at the YMCA, which had recognised the organisation as a leading advocate for children's rights.
The evidence presented by the committee indicates that the YMCA was alerted to the fact that it received the second lowest of four possible ratings in the audit of the Ministry of Education and Society from August this year.
