Staff members have provided evidence of witnessing such violations, including Lord being alone with the children, privately babysitting them, having them sit on his lap, telling them he loved them, and letting them play with his mobile phone.
Danielle Ockwell, who was Lord's employee and requested child safety training because she was concerned about his behavior, testified that Jacqui Barnat, the head of child services at the Caringbah YMCA, who was Lord's employee, was "very intimidating and often difficult to talk to".
