When he took office in 2008, Obama had 82 percent support.
And here I close the book.
Moving into the present is a rough awakening, like waking up from a dream.
It's hard to remember these optimistic days, they seem like distant memories, sad memories of wasted opportunities.
In the years since I cast my first ballot, there's been a real change.
It was definitely not what I imagined.
I recognize that Obama has achieved a number of great and diverse accomplishments from the Affordable Care Act to the withdrawal of our troops from Iraq to the end of the "don't ask, don't tell" policy after the killing of Osama bin Laden.
